### **Advancing Tokamak Rollup Hub (TRH) and Staking V2: Infrastructure Upgrades and Upcoming Milestones**

# ![][image1]2025 Tokamak Network (TON) Bi-Weekly Report \#7 : 5/1 \~ 5/15

### Highlight

This week, our primary focus centered on the Tokamak Rollup Hub (TRH) infrastructure upgrade and the ongoing Staking V2 integration. Notable progress includes advanced chain configuration, internal audits for L1 Contract verification, and preparations for UI service deployment. The second round of testing for TRH SDKv1 is scheduled to be completed on May 20, marking a critical step towards enhanced scalability.

### Ecosystem

#### 1.1. Staking Update

#### ![][image2]

As of May 15th, 2025, the total amount of staked TON has reached 23,924,641 TON. By staking with Tokamak Network, you contribute to this growing total and enjoy several benefits:

1\) Approximately [31% APY](https://simple.staking.tokamak.network/home)

2\) Various benefits such as airdrops

3\) The rights to participate in Tokamak Network DAO’s operations and decision-making process

### Technology Development

#### 2.1. Tech Development

Tokamak Network is an On-demand Layer 2 Platform and strives to provide various Layer 2 protocols to its users.![][image4]

* There have been 302 commits across 21 repositories in the Tokamak Network GitHub from May 1 to May 15\. The table above breaks down the number of commits by thematic pool, helping users understand the areas of active development. For more details on each repository and its progress, please visit the [Tokamak Network GitHub](https://github.com/tokamak-network).

2.2 Developing a Sybil-Resistance System for Decentralized Applications ([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/03cc941223844f30ba4473e98b1275a7?pvs=25)).

* Developed event listener and handler for the synchronizer.  
* Conducted an investigation into integrating Snapshot with SYB.  
* Completed the first version of stateDB, enhancing state consistency.

2.3 Developing Zero-Knowledge Proof-Based On-Demand Rollups ([Overview](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://medium.com/tokamak-network/project-tokamak-zk-evm-67483656fd21&sa=D&source=docs&ust=1734490765043963&usg=AOvVaw0KzcrtZJnAnxzX0oQiIp8Q)).

* Optimized the circuits for Tokamak zk-EVM,which will be used for state consistency.  
* Significantly reduce time and memory consumption for backend algorithms.  
* Working on implementing and planning a secure multi-party computation ceremony for Tokamak zk-EVM.  
* Working on a smart contract verifier of Tokamak zk-EVM.

#### 2.4. Developing Decentralized Staking and Governance ([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/49e44e989c514bd683e077c01cc8f143?pvs=25)).

* Addressed issues in the candidateAddOn contract; resolutions will proceed through a DAO agenda.  
* Prepared a research note focusing on attention testing for governance improvements.

#### 2.5. Advancing Developer-Centric Appchain Infrastructure ([Overview](https://tokamak.notion.site/1433390669554ae5b09e400f4c9c0fd4?pvs=25)).

* Implemented advanced chain configuration for Tokamak Rollup Hub (TRH) SDKv1.  
* The second round of testing for TRH SDKv1 is scheduled to be completed on May 20\.  
* Finalized the MVP plan for UI service deployment for chain deployment.  
* Conducted an internal audit for Staking V2 L1 Contract verification.  
* Integration of Staking V2 SDKv1 is actively progressing.  
* Cross-trade is paused for two weeks to accelerate the Staking V2 audit and integration processes.  
* Research on DA Integration with Thanos Stack continues, with one Medium article currently under review and scheduled for release next week.

### Community

3.1. FAQ

These are some of the FAQs from the community. Please check the section below.

* **How to contribute to the Tokamak Network?**

1. **Grant program**: create your own project and apply for [GranTON](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Grant-Program-GranTON-f2384b458ea341a0987c7e73a909aa21?pvs=4)**.**  
2. **Full time**: [apply for a full-time position](https://recruit.wanted.co.kr/p/QVxQS0MVRm5HWEpb) with compensation and get paid in USDT/USDC in addition to the [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) grant paid by GranTON projects.  
3. **Part time**: apply for a part-time position in GranTON projects to expect to receive [TON](https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/tokamak-network) (TOKAMAK) rewards. Please contact the [project leader (owner)](https://www.notion.so/Tokamak-Network-Onboarding-523bc627bd374326b5dfbec3d3b0a8e1?pvs=21) directly and discuss with them.

* **How can I contact you if I would like to collaborate with the Tokamak Network team?**

  Thank you for your interest in collaborating with the Tokamak Network team. We are open to various forms of collaboration that foster Tokamak Network ecosystem growth and value.

  To discuss a potential collaboration, please send a brief description of your proposal to hello@tokamak.network, and we will review it and respond as soon as possible.
